
[1]indecency

   INDE'CENCY, n. [L. indecens, indeceo; in and deceo, to become.]

   That which is unbecoming in language or manners; any action or behavior
   which is deemed a violation of modesty, or an offense to delicacy, as
   rude or wanton actions, obscene language, and whatever tends to excite
   a blush in a spectator. Extreme assurance or impudence may also be
   deemed indecency of behavior towards superiors. [See Indecorum.]
